--VALUES--('28', '4.95616E+15', 'CGTN', '2023-10-12 23:30', "#问道新丝路#【求实论事 | 中巴经济走廊助力巴基斯坦摆脱能源危机】巴基斯坦前规划与发展部长阿赫桑·伊克巴尔在接受CGTN主持人许钦铎采访时表示，巴基斯坦在中巴经济走廊（CPEC）支持下，不仅告别了电力短缺，还实现了电力自给自足，能源结构趋于平衡。下一阶段，中巴将推进经济走廊“升级版”建设，共建增长走廊、民生走廊、创新走廊、绿色走廊、开放走廊，通过发展互联互通，巴基斯坦未来或可联动南亚、中国、中亚和中东，共同打造一个拥有30多亿人口的巨大经济区。#丝路上的新征程# Under the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor (CPEC), power shortages in Pakistan have been eliminated, making the country self-sufficient in power generation. This initiative has also attracted investment in renewable energy, specifically solar and wind energy, creating a well-balanced energy portfolio. Ahsan Iqbal, former Federal Minister for Planning &amp; Development of Pakistan, has confirmed these advancements and said the next challenge for Pakistan is to transition from fossil fuel dependence to solar energy. Recently, the vice premier of China's state council visited Pakistan and proposed an extension of the CPEC by establishing five new corridors of cooperation, focusing on agriculture, livelihood, innovation, green economy and regional development. By developing these networks, Pakistan has the potential to create a vast economic zone in the future comprising of more than 3 billion people. CGTN的微博视频", '3', '0', '11', '139', '608.3万', 'm', '', '北京', '北京', '中国')
